151
00:13:08,641 --> 00:13:10,202
Okay, so I’ll say it again.

152
00:13:11,109 --> 00:13:12,547
I could love you forever.

153
00:13:14,354 --> 00:13:17,377
- Nathan, so could I but...
- So then why can’t forever start today?

154
00:13:28,529 --> 00:13:30,621
Ah, don’t have a view like this in Tree Hill.

155
00:13:34,420 --> 00:13:35,584
You wanna talk about Dan?

156
00:13:36,802 --> 00:13:38,045
Do you think my mom knows?

157
00:13:39,453 --> 00:13:40,293
I don’t know.

158
00:13:42,986 --> 00:13:43,939
Think she cares?

159
00:13:45,618 --> 00:13:46,263
Do you?

160
00:13:49,531 --> 00:13:50,498
You know Luke,

161
00:13:52,105 --> 00:13:54,291
Dan’s your birth father and…

162
00:13:55,694 --> 00:13:58,956
even though he’s never been in your life it wouldn’t be wrong to be concerned.

163
00:13:59,582 --> 00:14:01,326
Would it be wrong to hope he dies?

164
00:14:07,067 --> 00:14:11,965
Dan has a heart condition known as HCM. It’s a genetic mutation

165
00:14:12,052 --> 00:14:14,889
and causes the heart muscles to thicken…

166
00:14:15,244 --> 00:14:17,650
eventually; it prevents the heart from pumping blood.

167
00:14:17,807 --> 00:14:18,775
But why now?

168
00:14:18,955 --> 00:14:25,232
Sometimes cardiac arrest is bought on by excessive physical activity, even excessive stress.

169
00:14:32,415 --> 00:14:34,626
I’ve made so many mistakes Deb,

170
00:14:35,109 --> 00:14:36,578
with you and with Nathan.

171
00:14:39,394 --> 00:14:40,771
