250
00:20:49,898 --> 00:20:50,961
This is from Lucas.

251
00:20:52,753 --> 00:20:54,786
I’m sorry. I shouldn’t have hid it from you.

252
00:20:55,129 --> 00:20:56,086
But you did.

253
00:20:56,968 --> 00:20:59,066
I’ve been carrying around the fact that he left without a word

254
00:20:59,138 --> 00:21:01,248
and you’ve had the words the whole time and didn’t tell me?

255
00:21:01,330 --> 00:21:03,701
- I was going to.
- When?! After you read it first?!

256
00:21:03,782 --> 00:21:05,774
No! I wouldn’t do that, I promise.

257
00:21:07,668 --> 00:21:09,623
Whatever Peyton, we should head back.

258
00:21:18,994 --> 00:21:22,675
Listen, Haley, if you want, I can do this alone. You don’t have to come in.

259
00:21:23,099 --> 00:21:25,700
No, I’m okay. I want to.

260
00:21:26,069 --> 00:21:28,542
Oh good. I was hoping you’d say that.

261
00:21:29,951 --> 00:21:32,153
Besides we stuck together with my parents.

262
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:35,296
Hey, anybody home?

263
00:21:36,341 --> 00:21:37,554
Mom? Dad?

264
00:21:38,177 --> 00:21:40,242
- In the kitchen, Haley!
- Okay.

265
00:21:45,865 --> 00:21:49,094
No matter what happens next, I want you to know…

266
00:21:50,124 --> 00:21:51,778
if my parents say yes…

267
00:21:52,882 --> 00:21:54,015
I will marry you.

268
00:21:55,946 --> 00:21:58,090
Okay. Okay, yeah I would.

269
00:22:00,666 --> 00:22:01,404
Mom?

270
00:22:02,855 --> 00:22:04,501
- Hey baby.
- Hey.

271
00:22:05,146 --> 00:22:07,220
Well don’t just stand there; give me a hug.

272
00:22:09,497 --> 00:22:12,252
- You must be Nathan, I’m Marion.
- Hi.

273
00:22:14,961 --> 00:22:16,159
Is my mom here?

274
00:22:16,378 --> 00:22:17,730
She’s around here somewhere.

275
00:22:17,838 --> 00:22:19,594
Here’s that article, Marion.

276
00:22:20,290 --> 00:22:25,354
You know, how someone can actually type with their head up their ass is beyond me.

277
00:22:27,613 --> 00:22:31,120
Nathan. Did you climb through Haley’s window again

278
00:22:31,186 --> 00:22:34,064
or did you actually locate our front door this time?

279
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,644
- Mom.
- I came in the front door, Mrs James.

280
00:22:36,726 --> 00:22:38,170
Atta boy. You're hungry?

281
00:22:38,344 --> 00:22:40,545
Actually ah, can we just talk to you and dad?

282
00:22:41,145 --> 00:22:42,997
- Are you pregnant? 
- What!?

283
00:22:43,126 --> 00:22:46,194
- Pregnant, with child, bun in the oven.
- Mom!

284
00:22:46,332 --> 00:22:49,142
Lydia stop. You know that Haley’s a virgin.

285
00:22:49,511 --> 00:22:52,266
- Marion.
- And it’s a damn shame if you ask me.

286
00:22:54,170 --> 00:22:55,901
Can we just talk to you and dad.

287
00:22:58,072 --> 00:22:59,859
Alright, I can take a hint.

288
00:23:01,495 --> 00:23:04,436
Besides, your mother’s going to tell me every word of it.

289
00:23:04,637 --> 00:23:06,572
Call me with the details, Lydia.

290
00:23:09,782 --> 00:23:10,770
Is dad here?

291
00:23:14,692 --> 00:23:17,963
Jimmy! Kitchen! Haley’s pregnant!

292
00:23:21,819 --> 00:23:24,641
- Shall we sit?
- I think we better.

293
00:23:29,435 --> 00:23:30,338
Can I help you?

294
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,130
I’m his son.

295
00:23:43,897 --> 00:23:45,095
Is he going to die?

296
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:48,130
You should talk to your mom. I think she’s in the chapel.

297
00:23:52,091 --> 00:23:56,040
Alright, just to recap on the reasons to stay side, we got;

298
00:23:56,118 --> 00:24:00,828
Dan’s an ass, you were an ass, my new teaching job,

299
00:24:01,304 --> 00:24:04,771
we both get a fresh start, your mother and I laid out my heart

300
00:24:04,858 --> 00:24:06,522
and this apartment has a killer view.

301
00:24:07,592 --> 00:24:08,463
So what else?

302
00:24:09,968 --> 00:24:10,731
Nathan.

303
00:24:12,758 --> 00:24:17,002
Oh. Yeah, that marriage thing must have been tough for you.

304
00:24:17,550 --> 00:24:19,283
No, I meant for reasons to go back.

305
00:24:22,267 --> 00:24:25,517
I was wrong about him. He’s a good guy and…

306
00:24:26,404 --> 00:24:30,736
yeah, okay, him and Haley, it’s kinda weird but…

307
00:24:32,204 --> 00:24:33,279
I’m glad for them.

308
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:39,577
You know Luke, I’m really proud of you for getting to know Nathan.

309
00:24:40,457 --> 00:24:42,085
If you think you should go home…

310
00:24:42,955 --> 00:24:48,081
then you should but there are… things in Tree Hill that I’m not sure I can face.

311
00:24:49,387 --> 00:24:50,324
Like what?

312
00:24:51,574 --> 00:24:54,814
Just… something I’m not proud of.

313
00:24:57,794 --> 00:24:58,838
Look…

314
00:25:00,313 --> 00:25:01,399
I’m gonna take a little walk.

315
00:25:03,544 --> 00:25:04,318
Keith!

316
00:25:05,259 --> 00:25:08,695
I’m good, I just... gotta get a little air.

317
00:25:17,106 --> 00:25:19,232
- Mom.
- Nathan.

318
00:25:23,559 --> 00:25:24,294
What happened?

319
00:25:26,072 --> 00:25:28,970
I found him in the beach house on the floor.

320
00:25:30,481 --> 00:25:34,305
I called 911 but they said I might have called too late.

321
00:25:35,596 --> 00:25:37,311
Mom, it’s not your fault.

322
00:25:41,699 --> 00:25:45,109
Remember when you were little and you had to have your tonsils out?

323
00:25:45,662 --> 00:25:49,849
I came to this chapel that night and sobbed

324
00:25:50,850 --> 00:25:54,329
because I had the worst feeling that something was going to go wrong;

325
00:25:55,047 --> 00:25:56,720
that I was going to lose you.

326
00:25:58,416 --> 00:25:59,751
You didn’t lose me, mom.

327
00:26:02,676 --> 00:26:05,936
Yeah, we’re here for you Mrs Scott. Whatever you need.

328
00:26:07,017 --> 00:26:08,164
Thank you Haley.

329
00:26:10,145 --> 00:26:11,902
I guess I’m not ready to let go.

330
00:26:20,058 --> 00:26:22,540
We were… gonna tell you today.

331
00:26:23,484 --> 00:26:24,543
Tell me what?

332
00:26:25,095 --> 00:26:27,533
I love your son very much, Mrs Scott.

333
00:26:27,610 --> 00:26:29,847
Tell me what, Nathan.

334
00:26:31,762 --> 00:26:33,006
We got married.

335
00:26:41,915 --> 00:26:43,758
I must be losing my mind.

336
00:26:44,798 --> 00:26:47,347
Listen mom, we’ll talk about it later. When dad’s well.

337
00:26:47,441 --> 00:26:48,981
When dad is well?

338
00:26:49,118 --> 00:26:53,910
Your father is unconscious Nathan, plus he may or may not be my husband at this point,

339
00:26:53,989 --> 00:26:56,907
who the hell knows and now you’re telling me that you got married?

340
00:26:57,803 --> 00:27:00,219
This has got to be a joke.

341
00:27:00,865 --> 00:27:02,133
It’s not a joke, mom.

342
00:27:02,323 --> 00:27:04,397
- Mrs Scott, we’ve thought about... 
- Shut up Haley.

343
00:27:04,831 --> 00:27:08,519
You did this to your father. You’re the reason he’s here.

344
00:27:08,615 --> 00:27:12,041
- Mrs Scott...
- I said shut up. Shut your selfish little mouth!

345
00:27:12,118 --> 00:27:12,912
Mom!

346
00:27:16,583 --> 00:27:18,074
You walked away from him.

347
00:27:19,378 --> 00:27:20,975
And you helped him do it.

348
00:27:22,768 --> 00:27:24,233
You’re both to blame.

349
00:27:41,364 --> 00:27:44,421
Deb, Deb, what’s wrong? What happened?

350
00:27:45,966 --> 00:27:47,164
He’s gonna die.

351
00:27:48,383 --> 00:27:49,136
Who?

352
00:27:50,287 --> 00:27:51,184
Dan.

353
00:27:52,270 --> 00:27:53,489
He had a heart attack.

354
00:27:55,521 --> 00:27:58,669
Oh my god! Oh my god.

355
00:27:59,817 --> 00:28:01,045
He’s gonna die…

356
00:28:02,161 --> 00:28:03,607
and it’s all my fault.

357
00:28:10,654 --> 00:28:11,915
They got married?

358
00:28:13,661 --> 00:28:19,140
- That is not the Haley James that I know.
- You mean the Haley Scott.

359
00:28:20,773 --> 00:28:25,617
I just, I don’t know whether to laugh or cry or… throw up.

360
00:28:26,333 --> 00:28:29,297
I mean Dan’s in the hospital and Nathan is apparently married

361
00:28:30,378 --> 00:28:31,275
and Keith…

362
00:28:32,432 --> 00:28:33,424
Have you called him?

363
00:28:35,580 --> 00:28:36,242
Yeah.

364
00:28:37,536 --> 00:28:39,041
Talk about your bad timing.

365
00:28:40,742 --> 00:28:44,259
Oh, it’s just... it would be better if he were here.

366
00:28:44,847 --> 00:28:46,598
Keith is good in a crisis.

367
00:28:49,472 --> 00:28:52,527
How is it possible that they could even get married?

368
00:28:53,741 --> 00:28:58,816
Well, well, Haley James in my house between the hours of 8am and midnight.

369
00:28:59,067 --> 00:29:00,014
Hi, Mr James.

370
00:29:00,356 --> 00:29:03,220
Hello, Nathan. Did you come in through the window?

371
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:04,945
He found the front door.

372
00:29:05,296 --> 00:29:06,690
Nice work Nate.

373
00:29:07,238 --> 00:29:09,973
So, to what do we owe this surprise?

374
00:29:10,505 --> 00:29:12,496
Well, we wanted to talk to you daddy.

375
00:29:13,597 --> 00:29:15,927
Daddy? This is gonna be expensive.

376
00:29:17,719 --> 00:29:22,946
Okay, look. You guys know that I am an extremely cautious person…

377
00:29:23,095 --> 00:29:28,384
and I consider things from every angle and I don’t just, like, jump into things.

378
00:29:28,460 --> 00:29:30,677
Like getting to the point of this conversation?

379
00:29:31,011 --> 00:29:37,263
Mr and Mrs James… as you know, I’m emancipated from my parents and…

380
00:29:37,374 --> 00:29:40,089
I think you also know that I respect both of you very much.

381
00:29:40,206 --> 00:29:44,092
I think I know where this is going and here’s the thing Nathan;

382
00:29:44,210 --> 00:29:47,727
you see, if we adopt you, the making out with Haley is gonna have to stop.

383
00:29:47,866 --> 00:29:49,228
At least in public.

384
00:29:49,438 --> 00:29:52,213
Could you guys be serious for like one minute of my life, please?

385
00:29:58,535 --> 00:30:00,256
I’d like to marry your daughter.

386
00:30:09,082 --> 00:30:10,302
I didn’t see that coming.

387
00:30:13,015 --> 00:30:15,263
Dad, mom...

388
00:30:15,402 --> 00:30:18,283
I will discuss this with your father.

389
00:30:18,781 --> 00:30:19,676
You will?

390
00:30:21,422 --> 00:30:23,501
If this is what you want.

391
00:30:27,715 --> 00:30:28,585
It is.

392
00:30:30,318 --> 00:30:31,335
Brooke, wait up.

393
00:30:31,580 --> 00:30:33,639
- You shoulda told me about the letter Peyton.
- I know.

394
00:30:33,778 --> 00:30:35,933
Then why didn’t you? Why would you hide it from me?

395
00:30:36,695 --> 00:30:38,406
Coz we were having fun again.

396
00:30:40,125 --> 00:30:43,239
Brooke, having our friendship back has been really, really great.

397
00:30:44,018 --> 00:30:48,292
You know I… I figured Lucas is gone so it didn’t matter what was in the letter

398
00:30:48,354 --> 00:30:50,100
because it was just gonna come between us.

399
00:30:50,667 --> 00:30:51,984
Why would you think that?

400
00:30:54,103 --> 00:30:58,231
Remember when we used to get up every Tuesday morning and ride our bikes to the Mall?

401
00:30:58,317 --> 00:31:00,027
So you could buy some stupid CD’s.

402
00:31:00,109 --> 00:31:02,721
Yeah, and you could buy make-up your mom wouldn’t let you wear.

403
00:31:03,428 --> 00:31:07,087
We’d spend half the day in my bedroom just listening to music and putting on awful eye shadow,

404
00:31:07,205 --> 00:31:09,147
and that was just the Tuesdays.

405
00:31:11,134 --> 00:31:14,595
We used to do a lot of really great stuff until guys got in the way.

406
00:31:16,658 --> 00:31:19,724
I was actually just going to the mall with you to check out Roy.

407
00:31:20,186 --> 00:31:21,342
Brooke, we were nine.

408
00:31:21,475 --> 00:31:22,422
What’s your point?

409
00:31:24,988 --> 00:31:28,013
Okay, I am sorry, I should’ve shown you the letter but…

410
00:31:28,469 --> 00:31:31,290
considering our history, it scared me so…

411
00:31:32,506 --> 00:31:36,068
I just… I just wanted my friend back for a little while.

412
00:31:41,032 --> 00:31:43,293
Come on. God!

413
00:31:57,996 --> 00:31:59,277
Closed during the day?

414
00:31:59,799 --> 00:32:03,306
Oh, I guess my heart just wasn’t in it today.

415
00:32:06,202 --> 00:32:07,954
Come on in, Mrs Scott.

416
00:32:11,504 --> 00:32:15,851
I’m sorry, I really wish you could have been there but it was so sudden.

417
00:32:16,137 --> 00:32:17,013
Yeah.

418
00:32:20,044 --> 00:32:22,522
Is Deb here? I figured you must have talked to her.

419
00:32:22,742 --> 00:32:24,293
She had to go back to the hospital.

420
00:32:27,231 --> 00:32:28,810
She was really upset.

421
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:31,406
Dan’s not doing so well.

422
00:32:31,671 --> 00:32:34,446
I know, but I meant with me.

423
00:32:35,352 --> 00:32:38,588
- Does that surprise you?
- Yeah, little.

424
00:32:38,738 --> 00:32:43,002
I could understand if it was Dan but Deb’s always been really supportive of my relationship with Nathan.

425
00:32:43,110 --> 00:32:44,625
Yeah, when you were dating.

426
00:32:44,947 --> 00:32:46,058
Is that how you feel?

427
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:48,792
Haley, it doesn’t matter how I feel.

428
00:32:48,966 --> 00:32:50,273
It matters to me.

429
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:56,561
Haley… I know that you and Nathan are in love

430
00:32:56,647 --> 00:33:00,578
and you know that I was also in love in high school

431
00:33:02,079 --> 00:33:04,982
but sometimes, love fades…

432
00:33:06,339 --> 00:33:10,715
and, I just hope with all my heart that… it doesn’t fade for you.

433
00:33:15,783 --> 00:33:16,421
Hello?

434
00:33:16,908 --> 00:33:19,431
Hey, man. It’s Lucas.

435
00:33:19,851 --> 00:33:20,741
Hey, man.

436
00:33:21,474 --> 00:33:22,892
Crazy forty-eight hours huh?

437
00:33:23,465 --> 00:33:25,536
Yeah, yeah I guess so.

438
00:33:26,742 --> 00:33:28,028
So listen...

439
00:33:29,365 --> 00:33:31,924
I know this is weird for us but…

440
00:33:33,409 --> 00:33:35,611
- I just wanted to call because...
- Oh yeah.

441
00:33:35,928 --> 00:33:39,645
Yeah he’s still unconscious but, you know him,

442
00:33:39,733 --> 00:33:41,842
he’s just waiting to wake up on his own terms.

443
00:33:42,508 --> 00:33:45,267
Well look, I’m here for you okay?

444
00:33:46,354 --> 00:33:47,536
For you and Haley both.

445
00:33:49,359 --> 00:33:50,966
Just call if you need anything.

446
00:33:51,995 --> 00:33:53,062
Thanks Luke.

447
00:33:55,747 --> 00:33:59,373
So listen. How did this marriage thing happen anyway?

448
00:34:00,428 --> 00:34:04,386
The boy’s emancipated Jimmy. Haley just needs our permission.

449
00:34:04,473 --> 00:34:06,475
Need I remind you that up until an hour ago,

450
00:34:06,552 --> 00:34:10,484
this boy came and went through a second story window like a horny cat burglar.

451
00:34:11,451 --> 00:34:15,353
- How can you even be considering this?
- Jimmy, you know our daughter.

452
00:34:15,460 --> 00:34:19,854
She has never done an impetuous, hasty thing in her life.

453
00:34:19,988 --> 00:34:22,947
Most days, she’s more mature than we are.

454
00:34:24,461 --> 00:34:27,053
- They’re in love.
- They’re in high school.

455
00:34:27,232 --> 00:34:31,155
Besides, if it’s meant to be, it’ll still be meant to be after college.

456
00:34:31,281 --> 00:34:34,672
Okay; we forbid her to do it. She hates us.

457
00:34:34,891 --> 00:34:39,198
She keeps seeing him, maybe she gets pregnant, she drops out of school,

458
00:34:39,290 --> 00:34:42,397
- she turns to a life of prostitution.
- Oh stop it.

459
00:34:42,516 --> 00:34:46,784
Oh! There she is, smoking crack and sleeping in the gutter.

460
00:34:49,381 --> 00:34:54,102
Did you know that my parents forbid me to marry you?

461
00:34:55,607 --> 00:34:56,336
Why?

462
00:34:56,764 --> 00:34:58,883
Because they thought that we were too young.

463
00:34:59,196 --> 00:35:00,374
Well why didn’t you listen?

464
00:35:00,528 --> 00:35:02,032
Because I loved you.

465
00:35:02,899 --> 00:35:07,675
And in the end we got married all the same and we’ve made quite a life together.

466
00:35:09,191 --> 00:35:12,467
But I always loved them less for not seeing what I saw in you.

467
00:35:21,981 --> 00:35:24,699
So I’ve been thinking I’m done with boyfriends for a while.

468
00:35:25,830 --> 00:35:29,097
Right. Brooke Davis, solo?

469
00:35:30,019 --> 00:35:32,338
Relationships are just too hard.

470
00:35:32,881 --> 00:35:35,054
Hooking up with boys is so much easier.

471
00:35:40,673 --> 00:35:43,224
So I’ve been thinking, I don’t wanna read the letter.

472
00:35:44,903 --> 00:35:48,896
I mean you can, I just whatever it says, I don’t wanna know.

473
00:35:50,525 --> 00:35:51,456
Are you sure?

474
00:35:53,437 --> 00:35:55,353
I mean it’s not gonna change how I feel.

475
00:35:56,361 --> 00:35:57,509
About Lucas.

476
00:35:58,164 --> 00:35:59,387
Yeah, about him.

477
00:36:00,207 --> 00:36:01,661
Or you, or me.

478
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:06,275
I don’t know, aren’t you tired of measuring yourself by what guys think?

479
00:36:07,524 --> 00:36:12,567
I just… I need to stop chasing boys and focus on myself more so.

480
00:36:17,385 --> 00:36:18,398
I hear ya.

481
00:36:24,091 --> 00:36:25,423
Hoes over Bros?

482
00:36:32,735 --> 00:36:34,020
I hope it wasn’t money.

483
00:37:07,825 --> 00:37:10,638
This hasn’t been going on okay, it just, it just happened.

484
00:37:10,699 --> 00:37:12,241
Listen to me, you son of a bitch!

485
00:37:12,523 --> 00:37:15,742
Those are the last words you’re ever gonna speak to me. You are no longer my brother.

486
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:16,659
You understand that?!

487
00:37:18,041 --> 00:37:19,465
You do not exist to me.

488
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:22,614
Hey Keith?

489
00:37:25,154 --> 00:37:26,530
I thought I might find you here.

490
00:37:30,791 --> 00:37:36,520
Yeah I was just... standing here, listening to that voice in my head.

491
00:37:37,806 --> 00:37:38,738
And what’s it saying?

492
00:37:39,772 --> 00:37:44,088
It’s saying if we leave this place today, we may never come back.

493
00:37:46,099 --> 00:37:47,676
And what’s the voice in your heart say?

494
00:37:49,239 --> 00:37:50,820
Luke, you know that’s not fair.

495
00:37:51,968 --> 00:37:58,076
I mean, you know Dan’s... he’s a bad guy. You said it yourself; you hope that he would die.

496
00:37:58,372 --> 00:38:01,845
I said that for you. I know how bad you want this.

497
00:38:02,007 --> 00:38:04,302
Yeah, yeah I do want this, don’t you?

498
00:38:04,465 --> 00:38:06,565
- Yeah, I do but it just...
- But what?!

499
00:38:07,112 --> 00:38:08,710
Why should we have to give it up?!

500
00:38:10,291 --> 00:38:13,968
I mean he was never a father to you, he leaves your mom when she’s pregnant,

501
00:38:14,035 --> 00:38:16,692
he rides Nathan until he cracks under the strain.

502
00:38:16,734 --> 00:38:21,019
